<div class="crumbs"><a href="/index.html">Home</a> / <a href="/leagues.html">Leagues</a> / <span>ABL · Australia</span></div>

<div class="hero">
  <div class="hero-inner">
    <div class="hero-flag">Australia · Australian Baseball League · Summer Down Under</div>
    <div class="hero-country">
      <span class="hero-flag-emoji">🇦🇺</span>
      <div>
        <div class="hero-title">ABL</div>
        <div class="hero-full">Australian Baseball League</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="hero-lede">
      <strong>Summer baseball when everyone else is in winter</strong>. The Australian Baseball League plays its full season from November through February — Southern Hemisphere summer — making it <strong>the only professional pro league active during MLB's offseason</strong>. Six teams, strong MLB organizational ties, and an annual pipeline that has produced <strong>Liam Hendriks, Travis Bazzana, Glenn Williams</strong>, and Team Australia's WBC core. Every game free on team YouTube channels.
    </p>
    <div class="hero-stats">
      <div><div class="hs-num">6</div><div class="hs-lbl">Teams</div></div>
      <div><div class="hs-num">40</div><div class="hs-lbl">Games / Team</div></div>
      <div><div class="hs-num free-hs">FREE</div><div class="hs-lbl">Team YouTube</div></div>
      <div><div class="hs-num">UTC+11</div><div class="hs-lbl">AEDT · ET +16</div></div>
      <div><div class="hs-num">2010</div><div class="hs-lbl">Re-founded</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="page">

  <div class="watch-window">
    <div class="ww-title">⚡ When to Watch ABL from the US</div>
    <div class="ww-lede">Australia is <strong>16 hours ahead of US Eastern</strong> in summer (AEDT). ABL night games at 19:05 AEDT = <strong>3:05 AM ET</strong>. Weekend afternoon games at 14:00 AEDT = <strong>10:00 PM ET the previous night</strong>. The counterintuitive magic: <strong>ABL fills the MLB offseason void</strong>. When MLB ends in early November, ABL begins its full season.</div>
    <div class="ww-grid">
      <div class="ww-item"><div class="ww-val">3:05 AM ET</div><div class="ww-lbl">Weeknight 19:05 AEDT</div></div>
      <div class="ww-item"><div class="ww-val">10:00 PM ET</div><div class="ww-lbl">Weekend aft prev day</div></div>
      <div class="ww-item"><div class="ww-val">7:00 PM PT</div><div class="ww-lbl">West Coast prime</div></div>
      <div class="ww-item"><div class="ww-val neon-val">FREE</div><div class="ww-lbl">Team YouTube</div></div>
      <div class="ww-item"><div class="ww-val">Nov–Feb</div><div class="ww-lbl">Full season</div></div>
      <div class="ww-item"><div class="ww-val">MLB Off</div><div class="ww-lbl">Winter void filler</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-head">
      <span class="section-num">01</span>
      <h2 class="section-title">Where to Watch ABL</h2>
      <span class="section-sub">Verified Apr 2026</span>
    </div>
    <div class="platforms">

      <div class="platform-card free">
        <div class="platform-tag tag-free">Free · Per Team</div>
        <div class="platform-name">Team YouTube Channels</div>
        <div class="platform-cost free">FREE · Every home game</div>
        <div class="platform-desc">
          <strong>Every ABL team streams home games free on YouTube.</strong> Perth Heat, Sydney Blue Sox, Adelaide Giants, Melbourne Aces, Brisbane Bandits, Canberra Cavalry — all active channels. Search "[Team Name] Baseball" on YouTube. Free international distribution.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="platform-card free">
        <div class="platform-tag tag-free">Free · Hub</div>
        <div class="platform-name">theabl.com.au</div>
        <div class="platform-cost free">FREE · Official</div>
        <div class="platform-desc">
          Official league site aggregates team streams, schedules, standings, and stats. Good starting point for finding each team's YouTube live feed.
        </div>
        <a href="https://theabl.com.au" target="_blank" class="platform-link">theabl.com.au →</a>
      </div>

      <div class="platform-card premium">
        <div class="platform-tag">MLB Affiliate</div>
        <div class="platform-name">MLB Network · Select</div>
        <div class="platform-cost">Cable</div>
        <div class="platform-desc">
          MLB Network has carried ABL Championship Series broadcasts in prior seasons. The league operates in close coordination with MLB — player development partnership runs both ways.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="platform-card premium">
        <div class="platform-tag">Domestic Aus</div>
        <div class="platform-name">Kayo Sports · Fox Sports Aus</div>
        <div class="platform-cost">Australian cable</div>
        <div class="platform-desc">
          Kayo Sports is the primary Australian paid streaming home. Fox Sports Australia carries marquee matchups and finals. Geoblocked outside Australia.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="platform-card premium">
        <div class="platform-tag">Regional</div>
        <div class="platform-name">7plus · Channel 7</div>
        <div class="platform-cost">Australia broadcast</div>
        <div class="platform-desc">
          Free-to-air broadcast partner for select games and finals. 7plus catch-up streaming geoblocked to Australia.
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-head">
      <span class="section-num">02</span>
      <h2 class="section-title">2026–27 Season Key Dates</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="timeline">
      <div class="tl-item"><div class="tl-date">Nov 13, 2026</div><div class="tl-title">Opening Weekend</div><div class="tl-desc">All 6 teams begin · First ABL game tips off the Australian summer.</div></div>
      <div class="tl-item"><div class="tl-date">Dec 2026</div><div class="tl-title">Boxing Day</div><div class="tl-desc">Australian holiday double-headers · Biggest attendance weekend.</div></div>
      <div class="tl-item"><div class="tl-date">Jan 2027</div><div class="tl-title">Regular Season Peak</div><div class="tl-desc">Crosstown rivalries · MLB scouts visit heavily.</div></div>
      <div class="tl-item"><div class="tl-date">Jan 2027</div><div class="tl-title">ABL All-Star Game</div><div class="tl-desc">Mid-season showcase · televised on Kayo + team YouTube.</div></div>
      <div class="tl-item"><div class="tl-date">Feb 2027</div><div class="tl-title">ABL Championship Series</div><div class="tl-desc">Best-of-5 championship · Perth Heat are most decorated franchise.</div></div>
      <div class="tl-item"><div class="tl-date">Feb 2027</div><div class="tl-title">Asia Series Qualifier</div><div class="tl-desc">ABL champion competes in Asia-Pacific club championships.</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-head">
      <span class="section-num">03</span>
      <h2 class="section-title">The 6 Teams</h2>
      <span class="section-sub">ABL · 2026–27</span>
    </div>
    <div class="divisions-wrap">
      <div class="div-block">
        <div class="div-title">Australian Baseball League · 6 Teams</div>
        <div class="div-teams">
          <div class="team-row"><strong>Perth Heat</strong> — Perth · Perth Harley-Davidson Ballpark · Most titles · Western Australia dynasty</div>
          <div class="team-row"><strong>Sydney Blue Sox</strong> — Sydney · Blacktown Int'l Sportspark · Biggest media market</div>
          <div class="team-row"><strong>Brisbane Bandits</strong> — Brisbane · Holloway Field · Reinstated 2024 after hiatus</div>
          <div class="team-row"><strong>Melbourne Aces</strong> — Melbourne · Melbourne Ballpark · Victorian baseball home</div>
          <div class="team-row"><strong>Adelaide Giants</strong> — Adelaide · Diamond Sports Stadium · Growing following</div>
          <div class="team-row"><strong>Canberra Cavalry</strong> — Canberra · Narrabundah Ballpark · 2014 Asia Series Champions</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="did-you-know">
    <div class="dyk-badge">The Fact</div>
    <div class="dyk-title">ABL is the Only Pro League Playing During the MLB Offseason</div>
    <div class="dyk-body">
      When the last pitch of the World Series is thrown in late October, American baseball effectively goes dark for four months. Winter ball in the Dominican, Venezuela, and Puerto Rico picks up some of the slack — but those are short-season leagues with rosters full of MLB-contracted players. The <strong>Australian Baseball League is the only fully professional league that runs a complete 40-game regular season plus playoffs during the MLB offseason</strong>. November through February. That makes ABL the most valuable live baseball property for American fans during the void. And because <strong>every game is free on team YouTube channels</strong>, there's zero friction. Travis Bazzana — the #1 overall pick of the 2024 MLB Draft — developed here. Liam Hendriks won his first championship here. The ABL isn't just a pipeline; it's the <strong>one place where real pro ball exists in the dead of MLB winter</strong>, and it's ready for you every weeknight at 3 AM ET.
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="watch-window neon">
    <div class="ww-title">⚡ ABL This Week</div>
    <div class="ww-lede">See every ABL game during the Australian summer season — times in NYC/ET, YouTube links — in the <strong>Official Viewer's Guide</strong>.</div>
